HEADWORD: Helenin
<hw>Hel"e*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
neutral organic substance found in the root of the elecampane
(<spn>Inula helenium</spn>), and extracted as a white crystalline or
oily material, with a slightly bitter taste.</def> <-- used to induce
interferon production -- contains RNA -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

